Pure LSTM Implementation¶

In [2]:
class LSTM_base(nn.Module):
    def __init__(self, params):
        super(LSTM_base, self).__init__()

        self.hidden_size     = params['hidden_size']
        self.num_layers      = params['num_layers']
        self.p               = params['dropout_rate']

        self.lstm = nn.LSTM(timeSeries_input_size, self.hidden_size, self.num_layers, batch_first=True)
        self.fc = nn.Linear(self.hidden_size, output_size)

        self.dropout = nn.Dropout(self.p)

    def forward(self, x):
        X = self.dropout(x.timestampsData)
        timeSeries = self.dropout(x.timeSeriesData)

        out, _ = self.lstm(timeSeries)
        out = self.dropout(out[:, -1, :])
        out = self.fc(out)
        return out

    def get_input_weights(self):
        return self.lstm._parameters['weight_ih_l0']

In [37]:
class LSTM_full(nn.Module):
    def __init__(self, params):
        super(LSTM_full, self).__init__()

        hidden_size = params['hidden_size']
        num_layers = params['num_layers']

        self.lstm = nn.LSTM(timeSeries_input_size, hidden_size, num_layers, batch_first=True)
        self.hidden_fc = nn.Linear(input_size + hidden_size, hidden_size)
        self.fc = nn.Linear(hidden_size, output_size)

    def forward(self, x):
        X = x.timestampsData
        timeSeries = x.timeSeriesData
        
        out, _ = self.lstm(timeSeries)
        out = torch.cat([out[:, -1, :], X], dim=1)
        out = torch.relu(self.hidden_fc(out))
        out = self.fc(out)
        return out

    def get_input_weights(self):
        return self.hidden_fc.weight

In [62]:
best_model_base = torch.load("Models/LSTM_base.model")

class LSTM_prefilled(nn.Module):
    def __init__(self, params):
        super(LSTM_prefilled, self).__init__()

        hidden_size = params['hidden_size']
        num_layers = params['num_layers']

        self.lstm = nn.LSTM(timeSeries_input_size, hidden_size, num_layers, batch_first=True)
        self.lstm.load_state_dict(best_model_base.lstm.state_dict())
        self.lstm.requires_grad = False
        
        self.hidden_fc1 = nn.Linear(input_size, input_size)
        self.hidden_fc2 = nn.Linear(input_size + hidden_size, hidden_size)
        self.fc = nn.Linear(hidden_size, output_size)

    def forward(self, x):
        X = x.timestampsData
        timeSeries = x.timeSeriesData
        
        out1, _ = self.lstm(timeSeries)
        out1 = out1[:, -1, :]

        out2 = torch.relu(self.hidden_fc1(X))
        
        out = torch.cat([out1, out2], dim=1)
        out = torch.relu(self.hidden_fc2(out))
        out = self.fc(out)
        return out

    def get_input_weights(self):
        return self.hidden_fc1.weight
